requestBody.description:
This is an array of patchItems according to rfc 6902 http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6902
currenly we support only the 'add' operation and the path /FIMPolicy/Rules

Example:
[{
    "op": "add",
    "path": "/FIMPolicy/Rules",
    "value": {"type":"ExcludePath", "value":"a/b/c", "comment":"my comment"}
}]

singleNotificationIntegrationSettings.description:
List of the integration settings which are used to send immediate notifications
Constraints:  
    This currently supports a one integration setting for each integration setting for the following integration types: 
    one 'Http endpoint integration', Http endpoint can be of the following types: Webhook, Splunk, ServiceNow, QRadar, SumoLogic, Jira
    one of type: {SNS}
    one of type: {Email}
    one of type: {EventArc}
    one of type: {Slack}
    one of type: {Teams}
    one of type: Security Management System {GcpSecurityCommandCenter}
    one of type: Security Management System {AwsSecurityHub}
    one of type: Security Management System {AzureDefender}
    one of type: Ticketing system {PagerDuty}
